divs: sighting detailsi was driving south on kettle moriane drive 1\8 mi north of west bend wi. i glanced up at the half moon in the clear sky which centered in the upper wind shield when i noticed an unusual object moving west to east approaching the road i was driving on. it was approx twice the size of a twin prop plane, triangle shape (the bright half moon revealed the outline), with a luminous light at each rounded point. all three lights were pointed directly downward with the forward one being faded orange in color and the two rear lights being white. i pulled over and turned off the radio and opened the window to put my head out to get a better unobstructed view. the object made no sound as it traveled at approx 80 to 100 mi per hour at approx 800 ft alt. the entire sighting lasted 5 min until i lost sight of it beyond some trees. we have a local airport not far away and anything at this altitude should be comming from or going to it, but when i turned sw onto hihway d 2 min later it had bypassed the airport to the north headed east toward port washington and lake michigan.
trends: There have been 3 other sightings in West Bend
There were no other sightings in West Bend on or around October 25th 2009
Summary: Triangle shaped object traveling from west to east at aprox 80 to 100 mi hr at aprox 800 to 1000 ft altitude
